news.title: L&T Realty and CapitaLand India Trust to develop six million sq ft office spaces
news.para: Depending on the completion of these developments, CLINT expects majority of the capital commitment for the projects to start from H2 2024 onwards.

news.title: Over 15,000 objections & suggestions received on Navi Mumbai draft development plan
news.para: Now, the NMMC will soon conduct hearings on the suggestions and objections received and prepare the final draft to be submitted to the state government for further approval.

news.title: Raipur civic body to ease process for transfer of land ownership
news.para: Besides, all types of taxes can also be deposited online without going to the RMC offices. The existing method of name transfer in land cases takes more than two months to complete.

news.title: One year on, Nagpur development body yet to execute PMAY lease deeds
news.para: Stamp duty is charged around 7% of the total value of flat in the city. The total cost of a PMAY flat is Rs9.15 lakh, thus the stamp duty amount comes to Rs64,050.

news.title: Raze all unauthorised structures in Guntur: Civic body chief to officials
news.para: Reviewing the town planning department activities, the commissioner said it was unfortunate to see unauthorised constructions going on unabated in the city.

news.title: Submit report if a clubhouse is needed within Kharghar housing society: Bombay HC to Cidco
news.para: Justices Ramesh Dhanuka and Kamal Khata passed the direction on a 2018 petition by Spaghetti CHS at sector 15 with 4 buildings. They are part of a large layout of 9 buildings with 1456 flats that were constructed by Cidco as part of a mass housing scheme and completed around 2005.

news.title: Goa: Soon, builders & flat buyers can register sale deeds online
news.para: To partially resolve this issue, an e-registration facility for flats purchased directly from builders of housing complexes is on the cards, which is expected to do away with the requirement of visiting the office of the registrar concerned for the purpose.

news.title: Motilal Oswal Alternates plans to raise Rs 2,000 crore via sixth realty fund
news.para: The fund plans to deploy the capital in mid-income and affordable housing projects across Mumbai, Delhi-NCR, Pune, Bengaluru, Chennai, Hyderabad and Ahmedabad, while selectively investing in commercial projects as well.

news.title: SCDRC directs DLF Homes to pay Rs 1.35 lakh to home buyers
news.para: The forum also directed DLF Homes to execute the sale deed in respect of unit no A-1/33-GF for an area measuring 282.017 square metres or 3,035.60 square feet in favour of Anita Singh within 30 days.

news.title: Waterfield Advisors leases office space at Avighna House in Mumbai at record rentals
news.para: The firm has leased over 6,150 sq ft usable office space in the tower for a total term of five years. The deal assumes significance in the backdrop of the record per sq ft rentals attracted by any office property in the country’s most expensive market of Mumbai after a long gap.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh HC seeks norms for buildings along Narmada
news.para: Hearing a petition filed by Dayoday Seva Kendra alleging violation of no-construction norm within 300 metres on the banks of river Narmada, the division bench of Chief Justice R V Malimath and Justice Vishal Mishra issued the directives.

news.title: Buyers to pay 18% GST on plots bought from AUDA & Ahmedabad civic body
news.para: ​For almost a year now state GST officials have been issuing notices to the Ahmedabad Urban Development Authority and the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation, asking them to recover 18% GST from the buyer who bought a plot from these civic bodies last year.

news.title: Maharashtra government set to increase bid for Air India building to Rs 1,600 crore
news.para: The state plans to expand Mantralaya into the Air India building. Last month, deputy chief minister Fadnavis said that the state government was facing a space crunch to house government offices in Mantralaya and the annexe building.

news.title: MHADA may hike earnest deposits for MIG, HIG flats
news.para: The proposal, which will be soon placed before the housing authority, aims to charge 10% of the total cost of flat under the MHADA scheme so as to ensure applications from only genuine buyers.

news.title: MREAT orders Indiabulls' subsidiary & Lucina Land Development to refund buyer's money
news.para: The complainant, Sushila Gautam, had booked a flat in Indiabulls Green in 2013 and the promoter had agreed to execute an agreement for sale within 24 months of signing the booking form.
